      "values": [
        "2021 will get worse before it gets better",
        "Fearful of party stalwarts growing comfortable crossing him, the president has pushed to keep up the pressure and plot possible revenge scenarios against potential turncoats.",
        "Getting twitchy - Taiwan is ready to have �meaningful� talks with China as equals as long as they are willing to put aside confrontation so says President in NY message - worry about commando raids on islands after 1/21 military commission meeting in Beijing",
        "Missed chance with SoKo ? Japan�s new leader was the most popular kid in the class, but his obstinance, meanness, and ineptness have cost him support in Seoul. JB's to do list.",
        "Budget shortfalls and US sanctions generating growing dissent within the power ministries. Some signs of a chgnage of generational guard. Worry that Putin has supported DJT too openly with implications for links with JB administration.",
        "Where is he ? Kim Jong Un pens �heartfelt� New Years letter, gives�no sign of hallmark speech",
        "Realignments across the region - China trade ban paves the way for India as new market for Australia -- Rather Surprising�: New EU-China Investment Deal Causes Unease in India",
        "�Hong Kong�s rapid fall from its unique position as Asia�s World City. It has become a canary in the coal mine of�coercive PRC envelopment. N",
        "Tensions between Iran and the United States escalate, Iran�s foreign minister claims the United States is trying to fabricate evidence for war.",
        "Brexit done to EU's advantage/satisfaction",
        "Vaccine diplomacy in full swing. Russia and China will sell to Ems because DM's have soaked up western output - Algeria signs contract to use Russia�s Sputnik V Covid-19 jab, with mass roll-out of pioneering vaccine set for January - this should have been Sanofis market.",
        "NYSE starts process of delisting 3 Chinese telco companies",
        "US For at 7.5 . US government impairment hasn't gone unnoticed among the mischeif makers. Will Beijing flex its muscles ? Can Iran restrain its impatience to avenge Soleimani ? Will Kim do nothing ? Moscow watches and waits .",
        "Risk has risen to 6.6, 6.9 C19 adjusted. Senate Republican minoroty playing for DJT's supporters backing in 22 or 24 elections or to avoid primary challenge. Violence on Jan 6 a big concern",
        "With America distracted and the PRC economy seemingly going from strength to strength there are those in Taipei who are fearful that Xi will use the 100th anniversary of the founding of the CCP to show the world China is on the up.",
        "For Asian states the re-emergence of a more virulent form of C19 couldn't come at a worse time.",
        "Russia maintains influence across mid east, Africa and Belarus. Ukraine remains a concern for the Kreml which touts its nuclear force expansion. Links with PRC at a strategic level benefit bothMoscow and Beijing at this stage of the JB Presidency.",
        "Kim doesn't give his usual New Year speech. Rumours over his health circulating again. Will he remind Biden that in the last 4 years his ICBM technology has made major progress as has his stockpile of nuclear warheads. 8.1",
        "Cold Himalayan winters prevent movement along the LAC but behind the combat zone both sides are improving their logistic infrastructure and upgrading their systems.",
        "PRC courts are handing down long prison sentences on protesters and those trying to flee . Optimists say the financial infrastructure is unaffected. For how long ?",
        "Pressure on the Iranian government to deflect attention from slumping economy, failing social services and rampant C19 by revenge attack on Israel via Tehrans proxies in Iraw or Lebanon. Tense - reflected in 8.2 Gulf weighting.",
        "Brexit agreed to the EU's satisfaction . German CDU election in mid January. EU/PRC trade deal not well received in DC - autos before human rights. C19 roll out slow and haphazard just as more virulent C19 strain runs riot.",
        "Tourism revenues for the summer of 2021 now under threat from 2nd wave of C19.",
        "Biden needs to find a way of working with PRC to get the US econbomy moving in H1. Split in trade with hi tech prohibited ?",
        "Pelosi has chat with Milley about nuclear football. Orders must be constitutional. DoD would have liked this whole area to have been kept quiet. Gloat the word best used to describe Russia, China, Iran take on Capitol storming. Will Kim use chaos to test ?",
        "4000 daily C19 death number reached. Plots trending back to early '21 levels. Monet for vaccine distribution in States now approved. Still likely that most folks won't get it this year unless major investment.",
        "Latest government research raises fear the PRC using social media in concerted effoirt to undermine Taipei government - Taipei government, perehaps understandably, downplays this",
        "Tokyo and Seoul are at it again. The endless dispute between Seoul and Tokyo over wartime atrocities is flaring up again. On Friday, a South Korean court ordered Japan to pay out new reparations to a dozen former so-called comfort women, or victims of Japanese wartime sexual slavery.�",
        "If there's one major trend in the EU's eastern and southern neighborhood, it's growing Russian influence. The Kremlin skilfully exploits every crisis and conflict to advance its agenda. EU not a player or a power in these conflicts. US absent as well.",
        "North Korea forms new research center focused on hypersonic missiles",
        "The Indian government launched a $3.8 billion project meant to increase employment and investment in Jammu and Kashmir. The plan, which includes investment and tax incentives and promotes industrial development, runs through 2037",
        "pro-China Hong Kong officials have issued Intl arrest warrants for Danish MPs",
        "Israel deployed Iron Dome and Patriot air defense batteries to the southern city of Eliat. Together, the systems can defend against rockets, missiles, drones and aircraft. This is coupled with reports that Israel sent a submarine to the Red Sea. Both moves are seen as responses to threats from Iran.",
